The United States finished third in medals. He was arrested and released. Because of boycotts in 1980 and 1984, the Games were the first meeting between the Soviet Union and the United States since 1976 in Montreal, and matchups between the two nations provided some of the Games' highlights. Anthony Hembrick, a US boxer expected to win a gold, never got to fight; his coach misread the schedule and he missed the bus to the arena. _Sisters-in-law Florence Griffith Joyner and Jackie Joyner-Kersee led an American assault on the record books in track and field. 